<ol class="os-raise-noindent">
<li>Here are two patterns of dots.</li>
</ol>
<p>Pattern A</p>
<p><img alt="A pattern of dots. Step 0 has 0 dots. Step 1 has a row of 4 dots. Step 2 has 2 rows of 4 dots. Step 3 has 3 rows of 4 dots." src="https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/3c9a638d3d94a27279cdb7074d8c6646bb9233b2"/></p>
<p>Pattern B</p>
<p><img alt="A pattern of dots. Step 0 has a row of 2 dots. Step 1 has 2 rows of dots. The top row has one dot. In the last row, there are 2 dots. The left dot in the last row is in a column to the left of the column containing the dot from the prior row. The right dot is in a column to the right of the column containing the dot from the prior row. Step 2 has 3 rows of dots. In the top two rows, there are 2 dots in each row stacked on top of each other. In the last row, there are 2 dots. The left dot in this last row is in a column to the left of the left most column containing the dots from the prior rows. The right dot is in a column to the right of the right most column containing the dots from the prior rows. Step 3 has 4 rows of dots. In the top three rows, there are 3 dots in each row stacked on top of each other. In the last row, there are 2 dots. The left dot in this last row is in a column to the left of the left most column containing the dots from the prior rows. The right dot is in a column to the right of the right most column containing the dots from the prior rows." class="img-fluid atto_image_button_text-bottom" height="120" src="https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/09162edcf5ac5e0e874b3d0a4bf64423e00003e7" width="422"/></p>
