</ol>
</ol>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> 18</p>
<ol class="os-raise-noindent">
<ol class="os-raise-noindent" start="3" type="a">
<li> Which pattern shows a quadratic relationship between the step number and the number of dots?
      <ul>
<li> Pattern A </li>
<li> Pattern B </li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
</ol>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Pattern B</p>
<ol class="os-raise-noindent" start="2">
<li>Each expression represents the total number of dots in a pattern where \(n\) represents the step number.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Select two</strong> expressions that represent a quadratic relationship between the step number and the total number of dots. (If you get stuck, consider sketching the first few steps of each pattern as described by the expression.)</p>
<ul>
<li> \(n^2\) </li>
<li> \(2n\) </li>
<li> \(n \cdot n\) </li>
<li> \(n+n\) </li>
<li> \(n+2\) </li>
<li> \(n \div 2\) </li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> \(n^2\) and \(n \cdot n\)</p>
